# APB Based SPI Controller Verification

## Project Overview
This project focuses on the design and verification of an SPI (Serial Peripheral Interface) Controller integrated with an APB (Advanced Peripheral Bus) interface using SystemVerilog.

The APB interface is used for configuration and control of the SPI controller, while the SPI protocol enables serial communication between master and slave devices.

## Objectives
- Design and verify an APB-based SPI Controller.
- Validate SPI read and write operations.
- Verify APB transactions.
- Ensure protocol compliance through functional verification techniques.

## Features
- APB Slave Interface
- SPI Master Communication
- Register Read and Write Operations
- Functional Verification using SystemVerilog
- Assertion-Based Verification
- Functional Coverage Collection

## Verification Components

### Generator
Generates APB and SPI transactions for verification.

### Driver
Drives transactions to the DUT through the interface.

### Monitor
Captures DUT activity and forwards information for checking.

### Scoreboard
Compares expected and actual outputs to verify functionality.

### Assertions
Checks protocol correctness during simulation.

### Functional Coverage
Measures verification completeness and scenario coverage.

